WEBVTT

00:00.901 --> 00:02.369
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "WEEDS"...</i>

00:02.402 --> 00:04.905
MY NAME'S NOT
ON THE FUCKING BALLOT.

00:04.938 --> 00:07.875
I WON.
I FUCKING WON.

00:07.908 --> 00:10.110
I NEVER FILED
YOUR INTENT‐TO‐RUN PAPERS.

00:10.143 --> 00:11.512
OW!

00:11.545 --> 00:13.847
PEOPLE SEEM
TO LIKE WHAT WE'RE SELLING.

00:13.881 --> 00:15.582
THIS SHIT
IS ABOUT TO GET WILD.

00:15.616 --> 00:17.050
IT'S PAYDAY!

00:17.084 --> 00:18.785
WAIT A SECOND.
I DON'T GET PAID?

00:18.819 --> 00:20.554
ONCE YOU REIMBURSE ME

00:20.587 --> 00:23.557
FOR A NONREFUNDABLE YEAR
OF RABBINICAL SCHOOL,

00:23.590 --> 00:26.226
THEN YOU'LL BE COMPENSATED,
YEAH.
I QUIT.

00:26.260 --> 00:30.430
ALL OF AGRESTIC WILL
BECOME A DRUG‐FREE ZONE.

00:30.464 --> 00:33.066
I THINK YOU'RE TURNING AGRESTIC
INTO A POLICE STATE.

00:33.100 --> 00:34.535
YEAH!
YEAH!
YEAH!

00:34.568 --> 00:35.636
[ CHEERING ]

00:35.669 --> 00:37.738
THAT WAS AWESOME, SHANE.

00:37.771 --> 00:38.839
I'M THE NEW
HUSKEROOS GIRL.

00:38.872 --> 00:40.541
I COULD PUT YOUR MONEY
IN A TRUST.

00:40.574 --> 00:42.943
YOU'LL NEED ONE PARENT
TO BE SIGNATORY.
MY DAD.

00:42.976 --> 00:46.947
WE'RE LIKE THAT STORY,
"THE SCORPION AND THE TURTLE."

00:46.980 --> 00:48.749
"THE SCORPION
AND THE FROG."

00:48.782 --> 00:50.751
I BROUGHT YOU A BEAN PIE,
HEYLIA.

00:50.784 --> 00:52.719
JOSEPH,
AREN'T YOU LOVELY?

00:52.753 --> 00:55.622
HEYLIA JAMES? YOU'RE NOT
GONNA HAVE TO WORRY ABOUT HER.

00:55.656 --> 00:56.657
WHAT?

00:56.690 --> 00:57.791
SHE'S BEING TAKEN CARE OF.

00:57.824 --> 00:59.593
THERE'S REALLY NO PROBLEM
WITH HEYLIA.

00:59.626 --> 01:02.196
YOU GOT TO DIG THE WORMS
TO CATCH THE BIG FISH.

01:02.229 --> 01:03.597
HEYLIA'S BEEN DUG UP.

01:03.630 --> 01:07.467
AND I DON'T WANT TO
TALK ABOUT THIS ANYMORE.

01:07.501 --> 01:09.503
♪♪ BA‐DA‐WOP ♪♪

01:16.410 --> 01:19.379
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES ON THE HILLSIDE ♪♪

01:19.413 --> 01:21.882
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES
MADE OF TICKY‐TACKY ♪♪

01:21.915 --> 01:24.751
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES ON THE HILLSIDE ♪♪

01:24.785 --> 01:27.054
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES ALL THE SAME ♪♪

01:27.087 --> 01:29.857
♪♪ THERE'S A GREEN ONE
AND A PINK ONE ♪♪

01:29.890 --> 01:32.359
♪♪ AND A BLUE ONE
AND A YELLOW ONE ♪♪

01:32.392 --> 01:34.862
♪♪ AND THEY'RE ALL MADE
OUT OF TICKY‐TACKY ♪♪

01:34.895 --> 01:39.032
♪♪ AND THEY ALL LOOK
JUST THE SAME ♪♪

01:39.066 --> 01:41.702
♪♪ AND THE PEOPLE IN THE HOUSES ♪♪

01:41.735 --> 01:44.338
♪♪ ALL WENT TO THE UNIVERSITY ♪♪

01:44.371 --> 01:46.840
♪♪ WHERE THEY WERE PUT
IN THE BOXES ♪♪

01:46.874 --> 01:49.343
♪♪ AND THEY CAME OUT
ALL THE SAME ♪♪

01:49.376 --> 01:52.346
♪♪ AND THERE'S DOCTORS
AND LAWYERS ♪♪

01:52.379 --> 01:54.648
♪♪ AND BUSINESS EXECUTIVES ♪♪

01:54.681 --> 01:57.885
♪♪ AND THEY'RE ALL MADE OUT
OF TICKY‐TACKY ♪♪

01:57.918 --> 02:03.023
♪♪ AND THEY ALL LOOK
JUST THE SAME ♪♪

02:08.829 --> 02:11.565
[ BELCHES ]
OH.

02:11.598 --> 02:14.735
WOULD YOU STOP DOING THAT?
IT'S DISGUSTING.

02:14.768 --> 02:16.703
I CAN'T HELP IT.
I GOT GERD.

02:16.737 --> 02:17.871
"GERD"?

02:17.905 --> 02:20.407
IT'S GASTRO ESOPHAGEAL
REFLUX DISEASE.

02:20.440 --> 02:22.876
MY STOMACH ACID
KEEPS COMING UP THE WRONG WAY.

02:22.910 --> 02:25.712
SO IT MAKES ME BURP.

02:25.746 --> 02:27.881
IT'S VERY UNCOMFORTABLE.

02:27.915 --> 02:28.982
[ BELCHES ]
OH!

02:29.016 --> 02:30.584
OH, FOR CHRIST'S SAKE.

02:30.617 --> 02:32.920
I CAN'T SIT HERE WITH YOU
ANOTHER MINUTE.

02:32.953 --> 02:35.022
LET'S DO IT.

02:46.967 --> 02:48.902
FEDERAL AGENTS!

02:48.936 --> 02:52.606
GET DOWN ON THE FLOOR!
DON'T FUCKING MOVE!

02:52.639 --> 02:54.341
NOBODY FUCKING MOVE!

03:00.814 --> 03:03.050
WHAT THE HELL'S
GOING ON?

03:03.083 --> 03:07.387
KINDLY CURTAIL YOUR VULGARITY
IN OUR PRESENCE

03:07.421 --> 03:10.924
WHILE THE CALL TO ALLAH
IS UNDERWAY.

03:10.958 --> 03:13.760
THIS IS A HOUSE
OF WORSHIP.

03:13.794 --> 03:16.163
WHERE'S HEYLIA JAMES?

03:19.933 --> 03:21.535
WE ASK THAT YOU REFRAIN

03:21.568 --> 03:24.071
FROM ADDRESSING OUR WOMEN
DIRECTLY.

03:24.104 --> 03:25.672
WHEN A SISTER
EMBRACES ISLAM,

03:25.706 --> 03:28.876
IT IS NO LONGER HER CUSTOM
TO ANSWER TO MEN WHO ARE...

03:28.909 --> 03:32.112
UNFAMILIAR.

03:35.949 --> 03:37.985
SEARCH THE PLACE.

03:39.720 --> 03:41.755
THAT'S A NICE BUST,
SCOTTSON.

03:41.788 --> 03:44.091
[ BELCHES,
EXHALES SHARPLY ]

03:46.927 --> 03:48.829
SHIT.

03:48.862 --> 03:49.897
DO YOU THINK
THIS IS A GAME?

03:49.930 --> 03:51.832
DID YOU TELL HEYLIA
YOURSELF?

03:51.865 --> 03:53.967
OR DID YOU HAVE YOUR BOY
CONRAD DO IT?

03:54.001 --> 03:56.470
HEYLIA HAS
ALWAYS BEEN STRAIGHT WITH ME.

03:56.503 --> 03:57.905
YOU JUST WOULDN'T LISTEN.

03:57.938 --> 04:00.307
SHE'S A DRUG DEALER.
I'M A DRUG DEALER.

04:00.340 --> 04:01.808
TO KEEP THE HEAT
OFF OF YOU,

04:01.842 --> 04:03.644
I HAVE TO
PUT IT ON SOMEONE ELSE.

04:03.677 --> 04:04.912
I GAVE YOU
THE ARMENIANS.

04:04.945 --> 04:06.980
I GAVE YOU
THE ARMENIANS!

04:12.753 --> 04:13.854
YOU KNOW, THIS ISN'T ‐‐

04:13.887 --> 04:16.023
THIS IS JUST
NOT FUCKING WORKING.

04:16.056 --> 04:19.726
[ SIGHS ]
THIS ISN'T WORKING.

04:19.760 --> 04:21.762
"THE SCORPION
AND THE TURTLE."

04:21.795 --> 04:22.829
FROG.

04:22.863 --> 04:24.298
WELL,
NANCY, WE'VE TRIED,

04:24.331 --> 04:27.000
AND I THINK WE BOTH KNOW
WHAT NEEDS TO HAPPEN NOW.

04:27.034 --> 04:30.838
ACTUALLY, I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT NEEDS TO HAPPEN.

04:30.871 --> 04:32.306
WHY DON'T YOU TELL ME?

04:32.339 --> 04:33.974
ONE OF US
HAS TO QUIT HER JOB.

04:34.007 --> 04:35.209
WHY ME?

04:35.242 --> 04:37.144
DRUG DEALER'S NOT A CAREER.

04:37.177 --> 04:39.179
THEN WHY DO I
MAKE MORE MONEY THAN YOU?

04:39.213 --> 04:41.048
NANCY,
YOU GOT INTO THIS LIFE

04:41.081 --> 04:43.116
BECAUSE YOU DIDN'T
HAVE A CHOICE.

04:43.150 --> 04:45.819
I'M OFFERING YOU
ANOTHER CHOICE.

04:45.853 --> 04:48.255
WHAT CHOICE?
MARRY ME.

04:48.288 --> 04:50.023
FOR REAL.

04:50.057 --> 04:52.726
MAIL IN
THE MARRIAGE CERTIFICATE.

04:52.759 --> 04:55.896
TELL YOUR KIDS.
BE MY WIFE.

04:55.929 --> 04:57.064
HOW ROMANTIC.

04:57.097 --> 04:59.333
YEAH, WELL,
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO FORGIVE ME

04:59.366 --> 05:02.002
IF I'M NOT IN THE MOOD
TO SPREAD ROSE PETALS

05:02.035 --> 05:04.538
AT YOUR FEET.

05:04.571 --> 05:07.107
I THINK YOU SHOULD GO.

05:09.943 --> 05:13.981
WELL, YOU HAVE
A NICE FUCKING DAY.

05:20.921 --> 05:21.855
OUCH.

05:21.889 --> 05:23.423
[ DOOR SLAMS IN DISTANCE ]

05:27.928 --> 05:29.763
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

05:29.796 --> 05:31.632
[ TIRES SQUEAL ]

05:41.475 --> 05:42.543
THANK YOU.

05:42.576 --> 05:48.515
THE ENEMY OF MY ENEMY
IS MY FRIEND, SISTER HEYLIA.

05:50.951 --> 05:53.754
[ SIGHS ]
IT'S A SHAME.

05:53.787 --> 05:56.290
YES, IT IS.

05:56.323 --> 05:59.026
YOU SURE LOOK GOOD
IN WHITE.

05:59.059 --> 06:00.561
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:00.594 --> 06:02.829
WELL, ALL THEM RULES ‐‐

06:02.863 --> 06:04.598
AIN'T NO WAY
I COULD KEEP IT UP FOR LONG.

06:04.631 --> 06:08.101
DON'T SAY "AIN'T."
"AIN'T" IS A SLAVE WORD.

06:08.135 --> 06:13.907
WELL, I AIN'T NO SLAVE,
SO I CAN SAYS WHAT I WANTS.

06:13.941 --> 06:15.342
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:20.147 --> 06:22.683
ASSALAMU ALAIKUM.

06:27.120 --> 06:29.756
WA'ALAIKUM SALAAM.

06:29.790 --> 06:31.491
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

06:33.760 --> 06:35.495
YOU THINK IT'S POSSIBLE?

06:35.529 --> 06:38.298
YOU THINK THAT
A BLACK SCIENTIST NAMED YAKUB

06:38.332 --> 06:40.334
CREATED
ALL THE WHITE PEOPLE?

06:40.367 --> 06:43.237
COULD YOU SHUT UP
FOR 10 MINUTES?

06:43.270 --> 06:48.141
FOR 10 FULL MINUTES,
I DON'T WANT TO HEAR NO NOISE.

06:52.346 --> 06:53.580
[ DRILL WHIRS ]

06:53.614 --> 06:55.015
Man:
ALMOST DONE.

06:55.048 --> 06:58.519
IT'S GOT A FIVE‐INCH‐THICK DOOR,
THREE‐INCH WALLS.

06:58.552 --> 07:01.421
IT'S GOT SIX‐SIDED PROTECTION
AGAINST CONCENTRATED ATTACKS

07:01.455 --> 07:03.390
WITH MECHANICAL
AND ELECTRICAL TOOLS.

07:03.423 --> 07:06.360
WE KEEP OUR READY‐TO‐SELL
HARVEST IN HERE.

07:06.393 --> 07:07.928
AS WE ROTATE IT OUT,
WE FILL IT.

07:07.961 --> 07:09.930
NO CASH.
NO PERSONAL ITEMS.

07:09.963 --> 07:12.599
YOU AND ME ARE THE ONLY PEOPLE
ON THIS EARTH

07:12.633 --> 07:13.934
THAT KNOW THE COMBINATION.

07:13.967 --> 07:16.537
Man: RIGHT. I'LL SHOW YOU
HOW TO SET IT.

07:16.570 --> 07:19.173
YOU GOT FIVE NUMBERS.

07:19.206 --> 07:21.675
LEFT, RIGHT,
LEFT‐RIGHT, LEFT.

07:21.708 --> 07:22.843
FULL TURNS IN BETWEEN.

07:22.876 --> 07:25.345
YOU'LL HEAR A LOUD CLICK
WHEN YOU'RE DONE.

07:28.549 --> 07:29.850
SO, WHAT'S IT GONNA BE?

07:29.883 --> 07:35.355
WHAT ABOUT
6, 2, 6, 2, 9?

07:35.389 --> 07:37.357
WHAT IS THAT?

07:37.391 --> 07:41.094
IT'S "NANCY" IF YOU SPELL IT OUT
ON THE TELEPHONE.

07:41.128 --> 07:43.797
YOU THINK
THAT SHIT IS SLICK?

07:43.830 --> 07:45.732
LIKE NOBODY'S
GONNA FIGURE THAT OUT?

07:45.766 --> 07:47.234
AND NO KIDS' BIRTHDAYS,
EITHER.

07:47.267 --> 07:49.770
PEOPLE CAN
JUST LOOK THAT UP.

07:49.803 --> 07:52.472
[ SIGHS ]
OKAY.

07:55.042 --> 07:57.244
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

08:02.516 --> 08:03.650
HI.

08:03.684 --> 08:04.685
HI.

08:04.718 --> 08:05.886
YOU LIKE ME, DON'T YOU?

08:05.919 --> 08:08.822
YEAH.
YOU WANT ME
TO BE YOUR GIRLFRIEND?

08:08.856 --> 08:10.023
YES?

08:10.057 --> 08:12.092
I'M NOT GONNA KISS YOU
UNTIL I GET MY BRACES OFF.

08:12.125 --> 08:15.796
AND THAT WON'T BE FOR A WHILE,
LIKE MAYBE EVEN A YEAR.

08:15.829 --> 08:17.297
THAT'S OKAY.

08:17.331 --> 08:18.432
OKAY, THEN.

08:26.240 --> 08:28.208
<i>♪♪ HUSKEROO, HUSKEROO ♪♪</i>

08:28.242 --> 08:31.778
♪♪ YOU'RE BEAUTIFUL
IN ALL THE THINGS YOU DO♪♪

08:31.812 --> 08:35.916
♪♪ AND YOUR BRAND IS HUSKEROO ♪♪

08:35.949 --> 08:38.919
♪♪ HUSKEROO LETS YOU BE YOU ♪♪

08:38.952 --> 08:41.755
♪♪ HUSKEROO LETS YOU BE YOU ♪♪

08:41.788 --> 08:43.590
<i>THEY'RE JUST ROOMIER.</i>

08:44.690 --> 08:47.993
DID YOU SEE IT?
AT LEAST
THEY GOT HER HAIR RIGHT.

08:48.026 --> 08:49.895
SO, IF THIS THING
GOES NATIONAL,

08:49.928 --> 08:51.296
HOW MUCH MONEY
ARE WE TALKING?

08:51.330 --> 08:54.900
NEW DISHWASHER?
NEW HOUSE?

08:54.933 --> 08:55.968
IT'S ISABEL'S MONEY.

08:56.001 --> 08:57.803
THE LAW IN CALIFORNIA
CLEARLY STATES ‐‐

08:57.836 --> 08:59.805
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

08:59.838 --> 09:01.440
SO WE THROW SOME
IN A COLLEGE FUND,

09:01.473 --> 09:04.443
BUT THE REST IS FAIR GAME,
RIGHT?

09:04.476 --> 09:05.477
AFTER TAXES,

09:05.510 --> 09:07.980
AFTER WE PAY DOUG,
AND AFTER MY MANAGEMENT FEE.

09:08.013 --> 09:10.115
OKAY, FINE, MANAGER.

09:10.148 --> 09:11.817
CAN YOU LOAN ME
A FEW GRAND?

09:11.850 --> 09:13.819
WHAT FOR?

09:13.852 --> 09:16.455
CLOTHES.
I HAD MY CANCER PURGE.

09:16.488 --> 09:20.292
BUT NOW I AM IN THE PUBLIC EYE,
AND I HAVE NOTHING TO WEAR.

09:20.325 --> 09:22.294
YOU WANT TO TAKE ISABEL'S
HARD‐EARNED DOLLARS

09:22.327 --> 09:24.162
AND BLOW THEM
ON GLAD RAGS

09:24.196 --> 09:26.665
FOR YOUR STAR TURN
ON AGRESTIC ACCESS TV?

09:26.698 --> 09:30.002
YOU BOUGHT A MOTORCYCLE
AND A RIDICULOUS LEATHER JACKET.

09:30.035 --> 09:31.837
ALL RIGHT.
LET ME THINK ABOUT IT.

09:31.870 --> 09:33.705
NO.

09:33.739 --> 09:35.407
♪♪ HUSKEROO, HUSKEROO ♪♪

09:35.440 --> 09:39.778
♪♪ YOU'RE BEAUTIFUL
IN ALL THE THINGS YOU DO ♪♪

09:42.614 --> 09:44.783
ARE YOU OKAY?
YOU LOOK A LITTLE FRAZZLED.

09:44.816 --> 09:46.051
I'M FINE.

09:46.084 --> 09:47.986
WHO KICKS ASS?!

09:48.020 --> 09:49.988
UH, I'M GUESSING YOU.

09:50.022 --> 09:51.723
I TOTALLY KICK ASS!

09:51.757 --> 09:53.458
WHAT DOES
"KICKING ASS" ENTAIL?

09:53.492 --> 09:56.128
A GIRLFRIEND,
BUT THAT'S NOT ALL.

09:56.161 --> 09:59.631
DID A FREE CHEESE GRATER COME
WITH THE GIRLFRIEND?

09:59.665 --> 10:00.632
OH, STOP IT.

10:00.666 --> 10:02.868
I'M GONNA BE THE CLASS SPEAKER
FOR GRADUATION.

10:02.901 --> 10:04.836
SWEETIE,
THAT'S FANTASTIC.

10:04.870 --> 10:08.340
WAY TO GO,
LITTLE MAN!

10:08.373 --> 10:09.841
THE WHOLE
LOWER SCHOOL VOTED.

10:09.875 --> 10:12.144
I'M GONNA GO START WORKING
ON MY SPEECH.

10:12.177 --> 10:13.845
CONGRATULATIONS,
HONEY.

10:13.879 --> 10:14.913
THANKS.

10:14.947 --> 10:16.782
OH, ARE WE WORRIED?

10:16.815 --> 10:18.250
WHAT? ABOUT WHAT?

10:18.283 --> 10:20.786
THAT THEY'RE SETTING HIM UP
TO LAUGH AT HIM.

10:20.819 --> 10:22.621
THEY'RE LAUGHING
WITH HIM NOW.

10:22.654 --> 10:26.592
THEY THINK HE'S COOL EVER SINCE
HE TOOK UP YOUR CAUSE.

10:26.625 --> 10:27.926
WHAT CAUSE?

10:27.960 --> 10:29.761
"GO, DRUGS!
RAH, RAH, RAH!"

10:29.795 --> 10:32.064
HE DOESN'T KNOW
WHAT I DO.

10:32.097 --> 10:33.398
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

10:33.432 --> 10:36.101
YOU KEEP CLINGING
TO THAT RAFT.

10:39.771 --> 10:43.742
OKAY, THIS VOTE IS ON A MOTION
BY WALTER STRINGER

10:43.775 --> 10:47.946
TO REQUEST A VARIANCE
FROM ZONING REGULATION 11.6,

10:47.980 --> 10:50.415
FOR A FRONT‐YARD SETBACK.

10:50.449 --> 10:52.884
ALL IN FAVOR?
Doug: TRY 11.2.

10:52.918 --> 10:54.586
[ CRUNCHES ]

10:54.620 --> 10:56.388
EXCUSE ME?

10:56.421 --> 10:58.890
IT'S ZONING REGULATION 11.2 ‐‐
NOT 6.

10:58.924 --> 11:01.360
AND WALT IS
NOT ADDING A FAMILY ROOM.

11:01.393 --> 11:04.429
MNH‐MNH, HE'S ADDING
A GIANT GARAGE FOR HIS BOAT,

11:04.463 --> 11:05.931
WHICH IS GONNA
CUT OFF THE LIGHT

11:05.964 --> 11:06.999
TO HIS
NEIGHBOR'S DINING ROOM.

11:07.032 --> 11:08.200
READ THE PLANS.

11:08.233 --> 11:11.236
A FAMILY ROOM
DOESN'T HAVE CONCRETE FLOORS

11:11.270 --> 11:13.338
AND A DOOR
THAT'S OPERATED BY A REMOTE.

11:13.372 --> 11:15.674
YOU'RE NOT IN CHARGE HERE
ANYMORE, WILSON.

11:15.707 --> 11:18.343
LUCKY FOR YOU, OR I'D THROW
YOUR NAUTICAL ASS OUT OF HERE.

11:18.377 --> 11:19.411
REALLY.

11:19.444 --> 11:21.813
BUY A FUCKING SLIP IN
THE MARINA, CAPTAIN CHEAP‐ASS.

11:21.847 --> 11:24.983
EXCUSE ME.
YOU'RE OUT OF ORDER.

11:25.017 --> 11:26.485
[ CRUNCHES ]

11:26.518 --> 11:29.922
NOW, ALL THOSE IN FAVOR
OF GRANTING THE MOTION,

11:29.955 --> 11:31.957
RAISE YOUR HAND
AND SAY "AYE."

11:31.990 --> 11:34.159
AYE.

11:38.030 --> 11:39.998
ALL OF THOSE AGAINST ‐‐
"NAY."

11:40.032 --> 11:41.466
NAY.
NAY.
NAY.

11:41.500 --> 11:43.635
MOTION IS DENIED.

11:43.669 --> 11:44.937
FUCK YOU, WILSON!

11:44.970 --> 11:46.738
GO PLAY
WITH YOUR DINGHY!

11:46.772 --> 11:50.442
COULD WE PLEASE JUST
TURN THOSE LIGHTS DOWN A LITTLE?

11:50.475 --> 11:52.411
YOU NEED THEM
FOR THE PUBLIC‐ACCESS CAMERAS.

11:52.444 --> 11:54.279
I KNOW.
IT'S UNFORTUNATE.

11:54.313 --> 11:56.248
NOBODY LOOKS GOOD
IN HIGH DEF.

11:56.281 --> 11:59.451
IF YOU WOULD LIKE TO ADDRESS
THIS COUNCIL AS A CITIZEN,

11:59.484 --> 12:01.153
YOU CAN GO AHEAD
AND WAIT AT ‐‐

12:01.186 --> 12:04.890
COULD YOU STOP
WITH THE FUCKING SPOTLIGHT?!

12:04.923 --> 12:06.592
CHECK THE LANGUAGE
AT THE DOOR.

12:06.625 --> 12:07.693
FAMILIES ARE WATCHING.

12:07.726 --> 12:11.830
YOU KNOW, I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TRYING TO DO.

12:11.863 --> 12:13.699
I KNOW WHAT YOU'RE ALL
TRYING TO DO,

12:13.732 --> 12:15.767
AND IT'S NOT GONNA WORK.

12:15.801 --> 12:19.905
I DON'T NEED YOU
TO LIKE ME.

12:19.938 --> 12:21.873
HOW ABOUT
WE PUT THIS TO A VOTE?

12:21.907 --> 12:24.876
ALL THOSE WHO DON'T LIKE CELIA,
SAY "AYE."

12:24.910 --> 12:26.845
AYE.
AYE. AYE.
AYE.

12:26.878 --> 12:28.680
THE PUBLIC HAS SPOKEN.

12:28.714 --> 12:31.083
[ CRUNCHES ]

12:34.553 --> 12:37.389
Nancy: DAMN IT!

12:42.594 --> 12:45.063
SATURDAY'S DAD'S BIRTHDAY,
YOU KNOW.

12:45.097 --> 12:47.933
I KNOW.

12:47.966 --> 12:50.702
WELL, WE HAVE A LOT TO DO
TO GET READY.

12:50.736 --> 12:53.839
MAYBE WE'LL SCALE DOWN
ON THE PARTY A LITTLE THIS YEAR.

12:53.872 --> 12:55.340
LAST YEAR WAS KIND OF
A LOT.

12:55.374 --> 12:57.743
WHAT DID YOU GUYS DO
LAST YEAR?

12:57.776 --> 12:59.878
ATE HIS FAVORITE FOOD,
WATCHED HIS FAVORITE MOVIES,

12:59.912 --> 13:01.346
AND BEAT THE SHIT
OUT A PIÑATA.

13:01.380 --> 13:03.215
[ LAUGHS ]
THAT'S RIGHT.

13:03.248 --> 13:06.018
HE ALWAYS DID HAVE A THING
FOR PIÑATAS.

13:06.051 --> 13:08.754
DID HE EVER HIT YOU,
NANCY?

13:08.787 --> 13:10.289
I'M NOT FILLED WITH CANDY.

13:10.322 --> 13:11.490
HMM.

13:11.523 --> 13:12.691
SO, WHAT'S THE PLAN?

13:12.724 --> 13:16.061
WE'LL DO SOMETHING,
MAYBE JUST NOT THE FULL‐ON,

13:16.094 --> 13:17.462
ALL‐DAY CELEBRATION.

13:17.496 --> 13:19.932
WHY CAN'T WE JUST DO
WHAT WE DID LAST YEAR?

13:19.965 --> 13:21.934
[ SIGHS ]

13:21.967 --> 13:24.403
I'M NOT SURE
I CAN HANDLE IT.

13:24.436 --> 13:26.705
FORGET IT.

13:26.738 --> 13:29.908
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY,
HOW ABOUT A MINI CELEBRATION?

13:29.942 --> 13:31.977
ALL RIGHT,
UH, WE'LL JUST KEEP IT SIMPLE,

13:32.010 --> 13:33.478
JUST THE THINGS
THAT JUDAH LOVES ‐‐

13:33.512 --> 13:35.614
CHICKEN PARMESAN,
"WILLY WONKA" ‐‐

13:35.647 --> 13:38.617
THE ORIGINAL, NOT THE
LAME JOHNNY DEPP PIECE OF SHIT.

13:38.650 --> 13:42.387
A PIÑATA, LAP DANCE.

13:48.927 --> 13:51.263
CELIA.

13:53.832 --> 13:56.201
OH. UGH.

13:57.903 --> 13:59.738
HEY, TAKE IT EASY.
ALL RIGHT.

13:59.771 --> 14:01.673
I NEVER
SHOULD HAVE DONE THIS!

14:01.707 --> 14:03.108
THEY HATE ME!

14:03.141 --> 14:05.277
THEY HATE ME!
THIS IS ALL YOUR FAULT!

14:05.310 --> 14:07.879
GOD, IF YOU WOULD
HAVE JUST PUT A FUCKING LIGHT IN

14:07.913 --> 14:08.981
AT THE INTERSECTION!

14:09.014 --> 14:10.515
I WAS GOING TO.

14:10.549 --> 14:11.883
OH, RIGHT, YOU WERE?

14:11.917 --> 14:13.352
YOU WERE
BEING THIS BITCHFACE.

14:13.385 --> 14:14.987
I COULDN'T RESIST FUCKING
WITH YOU.

14:15.020 --> 14:16.154
YEAH,
AND YOU STILL CAN'T.

14:16.188 --> 14:18.490
CITY COUNCIL
IS THE ONLY THING IN MY LIFE

14:18.523 --> 14:21.159
I DIDN'T HAVE TO GET BAKED
TO GET THROUGH.

14:21.193 --> 14:23.362
YOU TOOK THAT AWAY
FROM ME.

14:23.395 --> 14:25.063
[ SIGHS ]

14:27.032 --> 14:29.801
HOW DID YOU KNOW
ABOUT WALTER'S BOAT GARAGE?

14:29.835 --> 14:30.969
[ SIGHS ]

14:31.003 --> 14:32.938
CELIA, EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENS
IN GOVERNMENT

14:32.971 --> 14:34.439
IS MOTIVATED
BY SELF‐INTEREST.

14:34.473 --> 14:36.942
SOMEONE'S ALWAYS TRYING TO
PUT ONE OVER ON SOMEONE ELSE

14:36.975 --> 14:39.678
SO THEY CAN GET SOMETHING
THEY WANT.

14:39.711 --> 14:42.881
WE'RE ALL JUST NOTHING
BUT A BUNCH OF SELFISH ASSHOLES.

14:42.915 --> 14:46.051
REMEMBER THAT,
AND YOU WON'T GO WRONG.

14:47.920 --> 14:50.055
THANK YOU.

14:50.088 --> 14:52.724
[ SIGHS ]

14:57.029 --> 14:59.665
CELIA...

15:01.533 --> 15:03.635
YOU SHOULD BRING SOME VODKA
TO THE COUNCIL.

15:03.669 --> 15:05.704
VODKA.

15:05.737 --> 15:07.005
THAT'S WHAT I USED TO DO.

15:07.039 --> 15:10.375
YOU THINK THEY LIKE ANYONE?
THEY LIKE A GOOD BUZZ.

15:10.409 --> 15:12.878
ARE YOU JUST
TRYING TO SET ME UP?

15:12.911 --> 15:14.913
WHY WOULD I DO THAT?

15:14.947 --> 15:17.316
'CAUSE YOU WANT TO
SEE ME FAIL.

15:17.349 --> 15:20.752
I MEAN, WHY ELSE
WOULD YOU COME HERE TONIGHT?

15:20.786 --> 15:23.755
I JUST HAD NOTHING ELSE
TO DO.

15:23.789 --> 15:26.091
VODKA, HUH?

15:26.124 --> 15:28.327
GREY GOOSE.

15:38.904 --> 15:41.206
[ VACUUM WHIRRING ]

15:47.045 --> 15:49.848
HEY. GO TAKE
THE KIDS SHOPPING.

15:49.881 --> 15:51.717
GET SUPPLIES
FOR JUDAH‐FEST.

15:51.750 --> 15:53.719
YEAH,
I CAN DO THAT...

15:53.752 --> 15:55.354
WITH MONEY
FOR BOTH PROVISIONS

15:55.387 --> 16:01.326
AND MY SERVICES
AS A NANNY/ASSISTANT.

16:01.360 --> 16:03.128
OH.

16:03.161 --> 16:04.863
OH,
THAT'S HOW IT'S GONNA BE?

16:04.896 --> 16:07.199
WELL, ACCORDING
TO MY CALCULATIONS,

16:07.232 --> 16:12.004
I WILL HAVE FULLY
REPAID MY DEBT TO YOU AS OF...

16:12.037 --> 16:14.506
MY NEXT EXCURSION
TO THE DRY CLEANER'S.

16:14.539 --> 16:16.942
I'D LIKE TO DOUBLE‐CHECK
THOSE NUMBERS.

16:16.975 --> 16:18.443
THEY'RE ROUGH ESTIMATES,
REALLY.

16:18.477 --> 16:22.748
THEY'RE MORE PROJECTIONS...
TAKING INFLATION INTO ACCOUNT.

16:22.781 --> 16:25.784
I GOT ANOTHER BILL TODAY
FROM YOUR OLD ALMA MATER ‐‐

16:25.817 --> 16:28.553
HAMADASH
LA BLAH‐BLAH BLAH?

16:28.587 --> 16:30.188
OVER $5,000.

16:30.222 --> 16:32.357
HAMIDRASH L'TORAH ‐‐

16:32.391 --> 16:34.359
AND THAT HAPPENS
TO BE TAX‐DEDUCTIBLE.

16:34.393 --> 16:36.261
I DON'T PAY TAXES,
YOU IDIOT.

16:36.295 --> 16:39.264
THERE'S A BIG HARVEST COMING UP
IN A COUPLE OF WEEKS.

16:39.298 --> 16:41.366
WHY DON'T YOU COME BACK
AND HELP?

16:41.400 --> 16:43.168
I'LL PUT YOU
ON THE PAYROLL.

16:43.201 --> 16:46.071
I WANT MORE THAN SANJAY.

16:46.104 --> 16:47.139
FORGET IT.

16:47.172 --> 16:48.807
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

16:48.840 --> 16:50.375
YEAH, I'LL TAKE IT.

16:50.409 --> 16:52.144
WELCOME BACK.

16:57.149 --> 16:59.651
JELLY BEANS
FOR THE PIÑATA.

16:59.685 --> 17:00.986
DAD HATED JELLY BEANS.

17:01.019 --> 17:02.120
HE LIKED
THE CHERRY ONES.

17:02.154 --> 17:03.789
HE SAID THEY TASTE
LIKE COUGH SYRUP.

17:03.822 --> 17:06.892
THE ONLY CANDY YOUR FATHER
REALLY LIKED IS ALMOND JOY.

17:06.925 --> 17:09.194
DON'T ASK ME WHY.
BUT GET WHAT YOU WANT.

17:09.227 --> 17:11.597
NOT IF DAD HATED THEM.

17:13.966 --> 17:15.467
YAEL.

17:16.935 --> 17:18.470
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

17:19.938 --> 17:21.940
WHAT WAS DAD LIKE
BEFORE HE MET MOM?

17:21.974 --> 17:23.408
UH, HE DIDN'T SMELL
AS GOOD,

17:23.442 --> 17:27.412
BUT HE WAS THE GOLDEN BOY
TO MY BLACK SHEEP.

17:27.446 --> 17:29.414
HE DID EVERYTHING RIGHT ‐‐
A MOTHER'S DREAM.

17:29.448 --> 17:33.085
HARDWORKING,
ATHLETIC, AMBITIOUS.

17:33.118 --> 17:34.419
THAT WASN'T
GETTING HIM LAID,

17:34.453 --> 17:36.922
SO HE WENT THROUGH
A TORTURED‐ARTIST PHASE.

17:36.955 --> 17:38.257
WHERE ARE HIS PAINTINGS?

17:38.290 --> 17:39.925
NO, NO, NO,
NOT THAT KIND OF ARTIST.

17:39.958 --> 17:42.261
A PERFORMANCE ARTIST ‐‐
HE DID WEIRD STUFF

17:42.294 --> 17:44.896
LIKE PAINT HIS WHOLE BODY SILVER
AND STAND NAKED

17:44.930 --> 17:48.934
ON THE WAR MEMORIAL
RECITING BAD POETRY.

17:48.967 --> 17:49.868
WHY?

17:49.902 --> 17:51.236
TO GET LAID.
IT WORKED, TOO.

17:51.270 --> 17:53.538
HE MET YOUR MOM WHEN
HE HIRED HER TO DANCE BAREFOOT

17:53.572 --> 17:58.043
IN HIS "FEET ME IN ST. LOUIS"
INSTALLATION.

17:58.076 --> 17:59.912
BUT HE WAS ALWAYS BROKE.
[ LAUGHS ]

17:59.945 --> 18:01.747
IT WASN'T
REALLY HIS TRUE NATURE,

18:01.780 --> 18:03.382
AND YOUR MOM
WANTED KIDS, SO...

18:03.415 --> 18:05.317
HE TOOK
HIS ENGINEERING DEGREE,

18:05.350 --> 18:08.921
GOT A REAL JOB,
MOVED TO SUBURBIA.

18:08.954 --> 18:12.391
I'M NEVER GETTING MARRIED.
IT'S DEATH.

18:12.424 --> 18:15.394
YOU'RE A LITTLE YOUNG
TO HAVE REACHED THAT CONCLUSION.

18:15.427 --> 18:17.596
HOW COME YOU'RE NOT MARRIED,
UNCLE ANDY?

18:17.629 --> 18:18.931
'CAUSE IT'S DEATH.

18:18.964 --> 18:21.166
RIGHT HERE. HERE WE GO.

18:29.641 --> 18:36.148
SO, ELAINE ROBERTS' BROTHER
OWNS GREEN GRASS LANDSCAPING.

18:36.181 --> 18:38.483
OH, YEAH,
SHE GAVE HIM A NO‐BID CONTRACT

18:38.517 --> 18:40.686
TO MAINTAIN ALL THE PARKS
AND THE MEDIANS

18:40.719 --> 18:42.154
THE MINUTE
SHE GOT ELECTED.

18:42.187 --> 18:44.790
HE OVERCHARGES
LIKE HALLIBURTON,

18:44.823 --> 18:47.492
BUT YOU'VE GOT TO LOVE
THE FLOWERING JACARANDA TREES

18:47.526 --> 18:49.494
HE PUT OUT
BY THE BALL FIELDS.

18:49.528 --> 18:51.496
AND TOM BENDER
OWNS ALL OF OUR SCHOOL BUSES.

18:51.530 --> 18:54.166
HE BOUGHT THEM FROM THE TOWN
AND THEN RENTS THEM BACK TO US

18:54.199 --> 18:56.969
FOR TWICE WHAT HE PAID,
WHICH WAS ACTUALLY MY IDEA.

18:57.002 --> 18:58.470
BUT HE WENT BEHIND MY BACK

18:58.503 --> 19:01.640
AND MADE THE DEAL HIMSELF
WHEN DANA AND I WERE IN HAWAII.

19:01.673 --> 19:02.674
WHERE DID YOU STAY?

19:02.708 --> 19:04.810
THE FOUR SEASONS, MAUI.

19:04.843 --> 19:06.478
I PREFER THE KEA LANI.
ME TOO.

19:06.511 --> 19:08.947
BUT DANA LIKES
THE MACADAMIA‐NUT PANCAKES

19:08.981 --> 19:10.349
AT THE FOUR SEASONS.

19:10.382 --> 19:12.584
$28 FOR FUCKING
CRUNCHY PANCAKES

19:12.618 --> 19:15.654
THAT SHE TAKES TWO BITES OF
AND THROWS OUT.

19:15.687 --> 19:17.122
YOU WANT ANOTHER ONE?

19:17.155 --> 19:18.991
NO, NO,
I SHOULD PROBABLY SAVE THAT

19:19.024 --> 19:20.292
FOR THE NEXT
COUNCIL MEETING.

19:20.325 --> 19:23.328
OH, RIGHT, THAT'S YOUR VODKA.
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:23.362 --> 19:27.633
WELL, THANK YOU FOR THIS ‐‐
THE 4‐1‐1.

19:27.666 --> 19:31.637
I NEVER REALIZED THERE WAS
SUCH A METHOD TO YOUR MADNESS.

19:31.670 --> 19:34.172
SIX YEARS ON A JOB,
AND YOU LEARN HOW THINGS WORK.

19:35.007 --> 19:37.809
ARE YOU...
HEADING OUT, TOO?

19:37.843 --> 19:38.977
ME?

19:39.011 --> 19:40.979
ARE YOU LEAVING?
NOW?

19:41.013 --> 19:42.481
SHOULD WE
GO OUT TOGETHER?
WHAT?

19:42.514 --> 19:43.982
NOT "SHOULD WE
GO OUT TOGETHER,"

19:44.016 --> 19:45.817
JUST SHOULD WE GO OUT
TOGETHER ‐‐

19:45.851 --> 19:49.221
OUT OF THIS OFFICE,
OUTSIDE?

19:49.254 --> 19:53.859
WELL, IT IS LUNCHTIME...
OUT THERE.

19:53.892 --> 19:55.193
DO YOU WANT TO
TRY THIS NEW LITTLE

19:55.227 --> 19:58.530
MONGOLIAN‐BARBECUE PLACE
BEFORE THEY GO OUT OF BUSINESS?

20:06.038 --> 20:08.874
What was that?

20:08.907 --> 20:11.109
I DON'T KNOW.

20:20.185 --> 20:21.987
I HAVE CONDOMS
IN MY DESK.

20:22.020 --> 20:24.523
DO YOU HAVE HERPES, WARTS,
ANYTHING?

20:24.556 --> 20:25.857
I'M CLEAN. YOU?

20:25.891 --> 20:28.527
I'M CLEAN.
I HAD MY TUBES TIED.

20:28.560 --> 20:29.861
FUCK THE CONDOMS.

20:29.895 --> 20:31.096
GREAT.

20:31.897 --> 20:33.465
[ MOANING ]

20:36.969 --> 20:40.339
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

20:41.974 --> 20:43.242
THIS ISN'T ALL SOME SCHEME

20:43.275 --> 20:45.677
TO GET BACK CONTROL
OF ISABEL'S MONEY, IS IT?

20:45.711 --> 20:46.979
THIS ISN'T SOME HOSTILE WAY

20:47.012 --> 20:48.747
FOR YOU TO GET BACK AT DEAN,
IS IT?

20:48.780 --> 20:49.848
I'M NOT SURE WHAT IT IS.

20:49.881 --> 20:51.083
ME, NEITHER.

20:51.116 --> 20:53.752
I'M NOT SURE
I CARE RIGHT NOW.
ME, NEITHER.

20:53.785 --> 20:56.922
[ MOANING ]

20:56.955 --> 20:58.056
MY COUSIN LIVE
IN A VILLAGE

20:58.090 --> 21:00.025
WHERE ALL THE BABIES
BORN ONE YEAR

21:00.058 --> 21:01.827
LOOK LIKE
THOSE OOMPA LOOMPAS.

21:01.860 --> 21:03.996
THEN THEY STOP
THE CROP‐DUSTING,

21:04.029 --> 21:06.932
AND THE NEXT YEAR ‐‐
ALL FINE.

21:06.965 --> 21:09.434
DO THEY DANCE
AND SING MORALITY SONGS?

21:09.468 --> 21:12.671
NO, BUT A LOT OF THEM ARE TOSSED
IN BARS TO MAKE A LIVING.

21:12.704 --> 21:15.874
I USED TO HAVE NIGHTMARES
ABOUT THE BOAT SCENE.

21:15.908 --> 21:17.676
I USED TO HAVE TO
CRAWL IN BED WITH YOU

21:17.709 --> 21:19.845
AND READ TO YOU
FROM THE REAL‐ESTATE SECTION

21:19.878 --> 21:21.847
TO GET YOU TO FALL ASLEEP.

21:21.880 --> 21:23.515
WHICH GOT ME INTO TROUBLE
AT SCHOOL.

21:23.548 --> 21:25.083
WHEN WE WERE
STARTING ROOSEVELT,

21:25.117 --> 21:26.919
I PROUDLY ANNOUNCED
TO THE ENTIRE CLASS

21:26.952 --> 21:30.088
THAT FDR STOOD
FOR "FORMAL DINING ROOM."

21:30.122 --> 21:31.590
Shh,
I LIKE THIS PART!

21:31.623 --> 21:32.424
[ MICROWAVE DINGS ]

21:32.457 --> 21:36.194
OH, CAN WE SAY
"CHICKEN PARMESAN"?

21:44.903 --> 21:47.739
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

21:47.773 --> 21:50.275
[ SIGHS ]

21:53.478 --> 21:55.581
NO. OH, NO.

21:55.614 --> 21:57.916
I PROMISE I WON'T YELL.
NO ULTIMATUMS.

21:57.950 --> 22:00.986
I JUST WANT TO TALK.
CAN I COME IN?

22:01.019 --> 22:02.187
BAD TIMING.

22:02.220 --> 22:04.056
WHAT'S GOING ON?

22:04.089 --> 22:06.825
Shane: MOM.

22:06.858 --> 22:08.827
BIRTHDAY CELEBRATION.

22:08.860 --> 22:10.495
WHOSE BIRTHDAY?

22:10.529 --> 22:13.899
MOM, YOU'RE MISSING
THE BEST PART.

22:13.932 --> 22:16.168
GUYS, PETER'S HERE,

22:16.201 --> 22:18.170
AND I NEED TO HELP HIM
WITH SOMETHING OUTSIDE

22:18.203 --> 22:19.504
JUST FOR A MINUTE,

22:19.538 --> 22:21.840
AND THEN I'LL BE RIGHT BACK,
OKAY.

22:21.873 --> 22:23.508
WHAT'S HE DOING HERE?

22:23.542 --> 22:26.645
IT'S DAD'S BIRTHDAY,
FOR FUCK'S SAKE.

22:26.678 --> 22:28.847
DINNER'S ALMOST READY.
LUPITA, SET THE TABLE.

22:28.880 --> 22:30.115
YOU HAVE HANDS.

22:30.148 --> 22:31.984
DO YOU KNOW
HE'S A D. E. A. AGENT?

22:32.017 --> 22:34.853
HUH?
WHO'S A D. E. A. AGENT?

22:34.886 --> 22:36.021
THAT PETER GUY.

22:36.054 --> 22:37.856
GET THE FUCK OUT OF HERE.

22:37.889 --> 22:39.057
I SAW HIM LEAVING HERE,

22:39.091 --> 22:40.993
AND HE HAD THIS JACKET ON
THAT SAID "D. E. A."

22:41.026 --> 22:43.629
SHANE,
STOP MAKING SHIT UP.
I'M NOT.

22:43.662 --> 22:45.464
"D.E.A." COULD
STAND FOR A LOT OF THINGS.

22:45.497 --> 22:48.100
NUH‐UH,
IT WAS THE SAME KIND

22:48.133 --> 22:50.669
I SEE ON THE NEWS
WHEN THEY BUST PEOPLE ‐‐

22:50.702 --> 22:52.337
THE EXACT KIND.

22:52.371 --> 22:55.507
WHAT EXACTLY
DID HE SAY TO YOUR MOM?

22:55.540 --> 22:56.508
I DON'T KNOW.

22:56.541 --> 22:59.811
WHEN I SAW HIM,
HE WAS GETTING INTO HIS CAR.

22:59.845 --> 23:01.446
HE LOOKED REALLY MAD.

23:01.480 --> 23:04.683
HE'S MOM'S BOYFRIEND,
ISN'T HE?

23:08.954 --> 23:10.422
I REALLY
HAVE TO GET BACK.

23:10.455 --> 23:12.424
I DIDN'T MEAN
TO INTERRUPT YOUR CELEBRATION.

23:12.457 --> 23:14.626
I DON'T LIKE THE WAY
OUR LAST CONVERSATION WENT.

23:14.660 --> 23:15.794
I WAS UPSET.

23:15.827 --> 23:17.829
I KNOW,
AND YOU HAD A RIGHT TO BE.

23:17.863 --> 23:19.898
I'M SORRY
I WENT BEHIND YOUR BACK.

23:19.932 --> 23:21.233
I WANT TO BE WITH YOU.

23:21.266 --> 23:23.368
WE HAVE TO
WORK THROUGH THIS.

23:23.402 --> 23:26.004
WE HAVE HUGE ISSUES,
PETER.
ALL COUPLES DO.

23:26.038 --> 23:28.707
I'M GUESSING OUR ISSUES
ARE PRETTY UNIQUE.

23:28.740 --> 23:30.075
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

23:31.743 --> 23:34.613
THIS ‐‐ THIS IS REALLY
NOT THE RIGHT TIME TO TALK.

23:34.646 --> 23:36.415
WHEN IS THE RIGHT TIME?

23:36.448 --> 23:39.051
WHEN IT'S NOT
MY DEAD HUSBAND'S BIRTHDAY.

23:39.084 --> 23:42.821
[ SIGHS ]
FAIR ENOUGH.

23:42.854 --> 23:44.089
I HAVE TO GET BACK.

23:44.122 --> 23:45.724
I'LL CALL YOU LATER.

23:49.261 --> 23:51.663
WHERE IS EVERYBODY?

23:51.697 --> 23:53.999
AFTER SHANE TELLS SILAS THAT MAN
IS IN THE D. E. A.,

23:54.032 --> 23:56.835
SILAS TELLS SHANE
HE'S YOUR BOYFRIEND

23:56.868 --> 23:58.837
AND YOU DON'T CARE
ABOUT JUDAH NO MORE.

23:58.870 --> 24:00.973
SO HE SMASHED THE CAKE
AND RUN UPSTAIRS,

24:01.006 --> 24:02.307
AND SILAS GO OUTSIDE

24:02.341 --> 24:04.543
TO FUCK UP THE STUCCO
WITH A BASKETBALL,

24:04.576 --> 24:06.878
AND ANDY GO UPSTAIRS
TO GET NORCHED.

24:06.912 --> 24:08.413
I EAT FROM STRESS.

24:10.015 --> 24:12.951
Shit.

24:12.985 --> 24:15.187
[ BANGING ]

24:22.427 --> 24:25.130
SILAS.

24:26.665 --> 24:27.833
SILAS.

24:31.336 --> 24:32.604
TALK TO ME.

24:32.638 --> 24:35.274
YOU'RE INSANE!
HE'S A FUCKING D. E. A. AGENT!

24:35.307 --> 24:37.943
YES, HE IS,
BUT IT'S OKAY.

24:37.976 --> 24:39.945
HE'S OKAY WITH IT.

24:39.978 --> 24:42.881
SO HE'S A CROOKED D. E. A. AGENT.
EVEN BETTER.

24:42.915 --> 24:44.917
PETER PROTECTS MY BUSINESS,
SILAS.

24:44.950 --> 24:46.118
WELL, MAYBE NOW,

24:46.151 --> 24:48.086
BUT WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN HE BREAKS UP WITH YOU?

24:48.120 --> 24:50.822
OR DO YOU THINK THAT
THAT'S NEVER GONNA HAPPEN?

24:50.856 --> 24:52.991
WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN HE DUMPS YOU?

24:53.025 --> 24:54.426
HE CAN'T DO ANYTHING
TO ME.

24:54.459 --> 24:56.628
BULLSHIT!
HE CAN ARREST YOU!

24:58.797 --> 25:00.065
I'M GONNA
TELL YOU SOMETHING,

25:00.098 --> 25:02.234
BUT YOU HAVE TO PROMISE
NEVER TO REPEAT IT,

25:02.267 --> 25:03.368
ESPECIALLY TO SHANE.

25:03.402 --> 25:05.971
SWEAR TO ME,
NEVER TO SHANE.

25:06.004 --> 25:07.806
FINE.

25:07.839 --> 25:10.976
PETER AND I
ARE TECHNICALLY ‐‐

25:11.009 --> 25:12.844
WE'RE...

25:12.878 --> 25:15.314
WHAT?

25:17.015 --> 25:19.818
WE'RE MARRIED.

25:19.851 --> 25:21.820
I KNOW IT SOUNDS CRAZY.

25:21.853 --> 25:24.957
IT KIND OF IS CRAZY, BUT
SOMETIMES YOU DO CRAZY THINGS

25:24.990 --> 25:27.125
WHEN YOU HAVE NO CHOICE,
AND I HAD NO CHOICE.

25:27.159 --> 25:30.996
IT'S A BUSINESS ARRANGEMENT ‐‐
PURE AND SIMPLE.

25:31.029 --> 25:36.635
[ SIGHS ]
I KNOW WHAT YOU'RE THINKING.

25:36.668 --> 25:39.871
I...LOVED YOUR FATHER.

25:39.905 --> 25:42.007
I STILL LOVE HIM.

25:42.040 --> 25:44.509
THIS HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH JUDAH

25:44.543 --> 25:46.678
OR MARRIAGE, REALLY.

25:46.712 --> 25:48.113
IT'S BUSINESS.

25:48.146 --> 25:49.881
YOU M‐MARRIED HIM.

25:49.915 --> 25:53.852
SILAS, I KNOW
HOW STRANGE THIS ALL SOUNDS.

